Speed optimizations (no accuracy impact):

Batching Phase 0: 10 comments per LLM call instead of 1. Same prompt per comment, just 10 in one request.
Batching Phase 1: 10 comments per LLM call instead of 1. Same prompt per comment, just 10 in one request.
Batching Phase 3: 10 themes per LLM call instead of 1. Each theme gets its own exact-copy prompt block inside the call. Plus deduplication — only maps unique primary themes, then applies lookup to duplicates.
Parallel Phase 0 + Phase 1: Both run at the same time using asyncio.gather instead of one after the other. Separate semaphores (60 each) instead of one shared semaphore (50).
Retry with backoff: Each LLM call retries up to 2 times with exponential backoff (asyncio.sleep(2 ** attempt)) on failure. Old code had no retry.
Alignment safeguard: Batch results are matched back to input comments using comment_index and response_id cross-validation. If anything misaligns, the batch is rejected and retried. Old code had no alignment check (wasn't needed for single-comment calls).

Minimum word changes required for batching:

Phase 0: "Student Comment to Analyze" → "Student Comments to Analyze" (plural)
Phase 0: "provide a single, valid JSON object with the final verdict" → "provide a valid JSON object with the final verdict for each comment"
Phase 1: "Analyze the single student comment below" → "Analyze each student comment below"
Phase 1: "Analyze this single student comment:" → "Analyze these student comments:"
All batched phases: {response_text} replaced by {comments_block} containing numbered [COMMENT_0] (ID=42) blocks
All batched phases: Output changed from single JSON object to JSON array

